cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of zero-shot learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method proposed in the paper involves learning embedding functions to map source and target data into a semantic space, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the use of attributes to represent classes is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
